INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52928, 'enUS', 'Tell me about the ancient, Malorne.', 'Tell me about the ancient, Malorne.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52929, 'enUS', '', 'Legends of the great white stag have persisted in my culture for as long as we tauren can remember. Malorne likely stood guard over the primal forests at the very dawn of the world. He was an ancient spirit, the very embodiment of nature\'s power and purity!$B$BLong ago, the greatest tauren hunters would track the white stag when the moon was full. To catch even a glimpse of his shimmering hide through the trees was said to bring great fortune to the tribe for a generation.$B$BDid you know that Malorne was the consort of the moon goddess?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52930, 'enUS', 'No, tell me more!', 'No, tell me more!', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52931, 'enUS', '', 'Yes, Malorne was consort to the moon goddess herself, the one the night elves call \"Elune.\" From their union was born Cenarius, the patron god of all druids and one of the most powerful creatures ever to walk upon Azeroth.$B$BBut listen to me, I ramble on.$B$BMalorne is an incredible force of nature, but he only interacts with the mortal races in times of dire trouble. Have you heard about his deeds during the War of the Ancients? ', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52932, 'enUS', 'Fight well, soldier. I need you to stay alive out there.', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52933, 'enUS', 'They are tokens of respect, purchased only with blood on the battlefield. Earning enough of these marks will be critical if we plan on winning this war.', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52934, 'enUS', 'To stand a chance in this battle against Ragnaros, we must gather allies who will gladly brave the scorched plains of the Firelands. And before we can recruit such allies to our cause - be they druid, soldier, or simple provisioner - we will need to give them reason to join us.$b$bCarrying even a handful of these marks signifies you as a hero of our cause. Gather them in the hundreds... and you will lead armies.$b$bAre you beginning to see the plan yet?', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52935, 'enUS', 'Commander Shadowsong, what are the Marks of the World Tree?', 'Commander Shadowsong, what are the Marks of the World Tree?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52936, 'enUS', 'And why is that, exactly?', 'And why is that, exactly?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52937, 'enUS', '', 'Back behind me, where you first came in, there is a large thermal vent, blowing hot air up and out of this place. Stand on top of the vent, and then... jump! The momentum from your leap should be enough to propel you up to the top.$b$bOh, one more thing - based on some reports I\'m hearing from fellow druids, make sure you watch your head on the way out.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52938, 'enUS', '', 'Of course. By the way: you\'ll find several smaller vents which behave the same way, deeper in the cavern. With time, you may learn to use them to travel more efficiently within the cavern - or simply as a way to torment those gutless flamewakers.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52939, 'enUS', 'How do I get out of here?', 'How do I get out of here?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52940, 'enUS', 'I think I understand. Thank you.', 'I think I understand. Thank you.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52941, 'enUS', '', 'Well, my master Morthis is really the expert, but I can share with you what I know.$b$bThey are not birds. Certainly, they fly, their wings have the appearance of feathers, and we even call them hawks, but that is where the comparisons to birds stop. In fact, it would appear that they have more in common with dragons: an affinity for fire, a solitary nature, and - based on what we\'ve seen - some indications of intelligence.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52942, 'enUS', '', 'Isn\'t it? However, they do differ from dragons when it comes to their lifespan. Whereas the dragons of our world can live for millennia on end, these fire hawks live brief lives, passing quickly from egg to adulthood to death.$b$bThough my master warns against making emotional connections to our studies, sometimes I can\'t help but feel sorry for them. They burn so brightly in life... but in death, they\'re quickly replaced and forgotten.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52943, 'enUS', 'What more can you tell me about these fire hawks?', 'What more can you tell me about these fire hawks?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52944, 'enUS', 'Fascinating.', 'Fascinating.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52945, 'enUS', 'What is there to tell? They\'re spiders. Just slightly more... flame-oriented than the spiders you and I are used to.$b$bThey bite, they spin webs, they spit burning venom, and they capture some of my best friends in cocoons of searing silk. Horrible little things.', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52946, 'enUS', 'No matter. These are not the spiders we need to worry about, however. Their queen, Beth\'tilac, is the true danger. Her webbed fortress lies to the east, beyond our reach. There, she is protected by an army of arachnids, all prepared to give their life for the queen.$b$bAnd they\'re huge, too! Believe it or not, the 12-foot-long spiders you see here are the small ones. That being said, while they may not be minions of Ragnaros in the literal sense, they are a danger to our cause and should be treated as such.', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52947, 'enUS', 'What can you tell me about these spiders?', 'What can you tell me about these spiders?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52948, 'enUS', 'I\'m sorry to hear that.', 'I\'m sorry to hear that.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52949, 'enUS', '', 'Not much, I\'m afraid. I\'m no druid, I\'m here to lead troops. Seems odd to me that Malfurion tried to plant a tree in the middle of a warzone, but... like I said, I\'m no druid.$b$bHowever, I can tell you this. NOTHING makes those fire elementals angrier than the idea of a big, leafy tree growing right in the middle of their homeland. If nothing else, when this tree grows to its full size, it will be a beacon of hope for our forces... and a thorn in the side of our enemy.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52950, 'enUS', 'What can you tell me about the Sentinel Tree, general?', 'What can you tell me about the Sentinel Tree, general?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52951, 'enUS', 'What happened during the War of the Ancients?', 'What happened during the War of the Ancients?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52952, 'enUS', '', 'Ten thousand years ago, when the demons of the Burning Legion invaded Azeroth, the ancients fought side-by-side with the mortal races. Many of the ancients met their end by the Legion\'s hand. Cenarius would\'ve been killed as well, were it not for the actions of his father, Malorne.$B$BThe mighty stag leapt into battle, his hooves crashing down on demon skulls and his antlers piercing their fiery flesh.$B$BThen Archimonde the Defiler took to the field of battle. After a fierce fight, he seized Malorne by his antlers and... and snapped the ancient\'s neck.$B$BBut as long as there\'s life in the world, can a force of nature like Malorne ever truly die?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52953, 'enUS', '', 'Go\'el - the one you call Thrall - his spirit has been scattered across the elemental planes.$b$bThe Twilight\'s Hammer thinks to shake our will... but we shall not weaken. We will not forsake Go\'el.$b$bHe has risked everything to save this world, and we\'ll do no less for him!', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52954, 'enUS', '', 'Let me know when you are ready to travel to Uldum. We will ask Cyclonas what he knows.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52955, 'enUS', 'I am ready to travel to Uldum, Aggra.', 'I am ready to travel to Uldum, Aggra.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52956, 'enUS', '', 'Fandral Staghelm has returned as a ... \"Druid of the Flame?\"$B$BI fear one of my own may be implicated in this betrayal!', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52957, 'enUS', 'Yes, $c, things appear bleak. But know that even as things appear to unravel, they do so with a greater purpose.$B$B<Despite his comforting words, Nozdormu looks stricken, if not ill.>', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52958, 'enUS', 'I wish I could aid you in your plight, mortal. But the blue dragonflight is in disarray, and there are other urgent matters here at the World Tree that I\'ve been sent to investigate...', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52959, 'enUS', '', 'The world-shaman - shattered by the hand of Fandral Staghelm?$B$BGreater powers are at work here. Ragnaros has pushed his strength farther into this realm than I would have imagined.$B$BThe Firelord must be stopped!', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52960, 'enUS', 'It is you again, $c.$B$BIs something wrong?$B$B<Alysra\'s tail flinches, and her eyes dart back and forth under their lids.>', '', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52961, 'enUS', 'You turned Fandral Staghelm over to the Twilight\'s Hammer. Why have you betrayed the dragonflights?', 'You turned Fandral Staghelm over to the Twilight\'s Hammer. Why have you betrayed the dragonflights?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52962, 'enUS', 'We are too late! They killed her, as Fandral predicted.', 'We are too late! They killed her, as Fandral predicted.', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52963, 'enUS', '', 'No, the Firelord has already claimed this one for his own. Do you doubt his power?', 26124);
INSERT INTO `broadcast_text_locale` VALUES (52964, 'enUS', 'Has the Earthen Ring sent you?$B$BOur efforts to heal the land must begin here, at the World Tree. I\'m glad you are here to witness this.', '', 26124);
